
The interview format:
Two 45 minute interviews designed to get signal on how you approach building/architecting systems. You’ll be given an open-ended system design problem and asked to walk through and whiteboard the system design, as well as think through issues around scaling, etc. 
One 45 minute interview that includes 1-2 coding problems. This interview looks at core problem solving skills, i.e. Knowledge of common algorithms, data structures, and how to apply them. You’ll “code” your answers on the whiteboard. We completely understand it has been awhile since you have coded on the white board and Lar’s has appropriately chosen and prepped that interviewer. 
One 45 minute interview to talk about your experience – how you approached certain projects, how you’ve worked with your team and your colleagues, CTO, etc. 
One 45 minute interview that is a deep dive into your management experience. How you build teams, grow engineers, etc. 
Example: Management Interview Questions:
What first principles/culture to do you to instill in your teams?
How to you go about instilling those principals and influencing behavior?
What would you view as your personal strengths?
How would your turn around a troubled project?
What do you look for when you hire an engineer?
What's your ideal team?
How do you deal with unhappy people on your team?

Example: Management Design Questions
Describe the current product you are working on and what is your role?
Why was the project important to the company?
What technology did you chose? Why?
What would you have done differently? How did you build a team?
How did the project effect other teams within the company?
Prepare for deep dive discussions on the technology behind the design.
How do you define the product strategy?
What is the biggest mistake you made in last couple of years and how did you deal with it?
 
Be prepared to talk about:
-Why you want to work at Facebook.
-Current projects.
-Why you want a change.
-What you hope to work on at Facebook.
-What you love about your current position
 
